  "texts": [
    "• Hadronic-Phase Transport Charmonium experience additional suppression through scattering with π and ρ mesons in the hadron gas via J/ψ +π → D + D *, D * + D, and J/ψ + ρ → D * + D *, D + D, with inelastic cross-sections taken from Ref.",
    "[227]; π and ρ mesons are assumed to be thermalized in the hadronic phase.",
    "• Initial quark/quarkonium distributions The quarkonium initial distribution in nucleus-nucleus collisions is treated as a superposition of quarkonium distributions in pp collisions.",
    "The quarkonium momentum distribution is obtained by fitting the experimental data of J/ψ distribution in pp collisions, with a further modification from CNM effects.",
    "In the regeneration part, where the charmquark momentum distribution is needed, it is taken as a kinetically thermalized distribution."
